Day 7: Full Virtual Contest + Analysis
Objective: Simulate real contest experience.

Practice (3 hours):
Participate in a virtual Div. 3 contest (choose one from 2023–2025)
Time yourself strictly 2 hours
Aim: Solve A, B, C (possibly D)

Analysis (1–1.5 hours):
Read all editorials
Journal: Mistakes, time spent per problem, new tricks learned
Rewrite any wrong solutions correctly


Week 3 Milestone:

Comfortable with sorting, binary search, basic math
Solved 50–60 problems total (including previous weeks)
Completed 1–2 virtual contests
Ready for greedy algorithms and basic graphs in Week 4

Keep pushing — you're now starting to think like a competitive programmer!
